@startuml
title Creating an isolated process with namespaces and cgroups

start
:Parent process holds default\nnamespaces and full view;
if (Create new process or detach current?) then (new process)
  :clone() with CLONE_NEW* flags\n(NEWPID, NEWNET, NEWNS, NEWUSER, ...);
else (detach current)
  :unshare() with the same flags;
endif
:Child runs in fresh namespaces\n(own PID 1, own network stack,\nown mount table);
:Attach child to a cgroup\n(cpu / memory / pids limits);
:Set up the mount namespace\n(pivot_root or chroot, bind mounts,\nnosuid / noexec / nodev);
:Apply seccomp filter\n(restrict syscalls);
:Drop capabilities;
:exec() the target program;
note right
  setns() lets another process
  later join these namespaces
  (for example, docker exec)
end note
stop
@enduml
